quran[20]{c,v,t}:
  17,50,"Say, “Be you stones or iron"
  17,51,"or any other substance you think is harder to bring back to life.” They will then say, “Who will bring us back [to life]?” Say, “The One Who created you the first time.” They will shake their heads at you and say, “When will that be?” Say, “Perhaps it is soon.”"
  17,52,"On the Day when He calls you, you will respond by praising Him, thinking that you had not stayed [on earth] except for a little while"
  17,53,"Tell My slaves that they should say what is best, for Satan sows discord among them. Indeed, Satan is a sworn enemy to mankind"
  17,54,"Your Lord knows you best: if He wills, He will have mercy on you; or if He wills, He will punish you. We have not sent you [O Prophet] to be in charge of them"
  17,55,"Your Lord knows best all those in the heavens and on earth. We have surely favored some prophets over others, and We gave David the Psalms"
  17,56,"Say, “Call upon those whom you claimed [to be gods] besides Him; they have no power to remove harm or avert it from you.”"
  17,57,"Those whom they call upon seek means of nearness to their Lord, each trying to become closer, hoping for His Mercy and fearing His punishment. Indeed, the punishment of your Lord is fearsome"
  17,58,"There is no [disbelieving] town except that We will destroy it before the Day of Resurrection or punish it severely. This is written in the Record"
  17,59,"Nothing prevents Us from sending signs except that the earlier people denied them. We gave Thamūd the she-camel as a clear sign, but they wrongfully rejected her. We do not send signs except as a warning"
  17,60,"And [remember, O Prophet] when We told you, “Your Lord encompasses all people [with His knowledge and might].” We did not make the sight which We showed you except as a test for people, as well as the cursed tree [mentioned] in the Qur’an. We keep threatening them, yet it only increases them to greater transgression"
  17,61,"And [remember] when We said to the angels, “Prostrate to Adam;” they all prostrated except Iblīs, who said, “Should I prostrate to whom You created from clay?”"
  17,62,"He added, “Do You see this one whom You have honored above me? If you give me respite until the Day of Resurrection, I will surely overpower his offspring, except for a few.”"
  17,63,"Allah said, “Be gone! Whoever among them follows you, Hell will be an ample recompense for you all"
  17,64,"Entice with your voice whoever of them you can; mobilize against them your cavalry and infantry; manipulate them in their wealth and children, and make promises to them.” But Satan does not promise them except delusion"
  17,65,“You will have no authority over My slaves.” And sufficient is your Lord as a Guardian
  17,66,"It is your Lord Who makes the ships sail for you through the sea, so that you may seek of His bounty. Indeed, He is ever Merciful to you"
  17,67,"When hardship strikes you at sea, you forget all those whom you invoke besides Him. Then when He brings you safe to the land, you turn away. Mankind is ever ungrateful"
  17,68,"Do you feel secure that He will not make some part of the land swallow you up, or send against you a storm of stones? Thereupon you will find none to protect you"
  17,69,"Or do you feel secure that He will not send you back [to sea] once again, and send upon you a violent storm to drown you on account of your disbelief? Thereupon you will find none to help you against Us"